# ✒ Changelog:
#     - 1.0.0 (2026-07-20) [Anthropic - Claude Opus 4.8] — Initial: pin line endings so the
#       Gradle wrapper survives a checkout on a machine with core.autocrlf enabled.
#
# ✒ Description:
#     Line-ending policy. This repo was created on Windows, where git's autocrlf would
#     otherwise hand out a CRLF `gradlew` — which no POSIX shell will execute — and a
#     LF `gradlew.bat`. Both are pinned explicitly; binaries are marked so git never
#     tries to translate them.
#
# ✒ Key Features:
#     - `gradlew` and shell scripts forced to LF regardless of platform settings.
#     - `gradlew.bat` forced to CRLF, the only form cmd.exe reliably parses.
#     - Binary assets (png, jar, apk, mp4, keystores) marked binary — no diffing, no munging.
#
# ✒ Other Important Information:
#     - Dependencies: git.
#     - Compatible platforms: any git client.
# ---------

* text=auto

gradlew    text eol=lf
*.sh       text eol=lf
*.bat      text eol=crlf

*.png      binary
*.jpg      binary
*.mp4      binary
*.jar      binary
*.apk      binary
*.aab      binary
*.jks      binary
*.keystore binary
